Quill Pen, requires an Ink Well to write. 
Guide to using Bongo's Writing System.

Commands list: Note: The commands use a Hash/Number Sign #.
#T#   Title: This is used to set a Title(name). For example type #T#My Title Here then use the Quill Pen on the item you want to Title.

#W#   Write: This is used to write a message for a description. Example type #W#My message here. then use the Quill Pen on the item you want to write on.

#C#text   Copy: This is used to copy the description of a target. Type the Command, then select the item you wish to copy from with the Quill Pen. Then use the Quill Pen on the item you wish to copy the text to.

#C#all   Copy: This is used to copy both the name and description of a target. Type the Command, then select the item you wish to copy from with the Quill Pen. Then use the Quill Pen on the item you wish to copy to.

#E#   Enter: This is used basically like the enter key pushed once. Type the Command then use the Quill Pen on the item you wish, then your next message entry will start on the line below your current message. Repeat this process to use more than once.

#R#   Reverse: This is used to undo your last description update. In case you make an error. Type the command and use the Quill Pen on the item you wish to be reversed.

#S#   Seal: This is used for setting a custom wax seal on a Wax-Sealed Letter, refer to Sealing Wax Description for details.

#F#   Finish: This is used to set an item as finished. Once set you finish an item can no longer be edited. This command is recommended if you wish to pass your items to other players. Type #F# then use the Quill Pen on the item you want set as non-editable.

Only items bought from the Penman(Scribe) can be written on.

Items:
Sheet of Paper: This has a 55 character maximum for its Title and a 1000 word maximum for its description.

Blank Book: Books have a 55 character maximum for their Title, but an unlimited description.

Bulletin Board Notice: This has a maximum of 30 characters for its Title and a 300 character maximum for its Description. This is to avoid clutter on Bulletin Boards.

Wax-Sealed Letter: Letters has a maximum Title length of 47 characters and a maximum description length of 1000 characters. Letters work differently than the other items. You can title them and write on them but their written message will not show up until their Unique Power is activated, this is to simulate the opening of a letter and breaking of its seal. Before being opened you may customise the description of a letter to simulate its wax seal, you can even choose a colour for the wax. Refer to the description of the coloured Wax's for further details.
Quill Pen
